BudKnight writes <i>"It looks like AMD is launching four new desktop processors, a new core, and
a new socket infrastructure today.
<A HREF="http://www.hothardware.com/viewarticle.cfm?articleid=531&amp;cid=1">HotHardware has tested AMD's two new
flagship processors</a>, the Athlon 64 FX-53 and the Athlon 64 3800+. The new
FX-53 no longer needs registered memory to function and the 3800+ has only 512K
of cache, but it gets an upgraded 128-bit memory controller. The usual
suspects also have reviews posted as well -
<A HREF="http://techreport.com/reviews/2004q2/athlon64-3800/index.x?pg=1">TechReport</a>,
